<!-- Section 5: The Verdict -->
<section class="compare-section">
  <h2>The Verdict: Stage and Complexity Drive the Decision</h2>
  <p>HubSpot vs Salesforce is one of the most common CRM evaluations in B2B sales, and the answer is more predictable than most vendors admit. HubSpot wins for teams that prioritize fast adoption, low total cost of ownership, and an all-in-one platform that covers CRM, marketing, and sales without requiring expensive implementation work. Salesforce wins for organizations with complex, non-standard processes that require the platform's deep customization capabilities.</p>
  <p>The inflection point is typically around 50–100 reps or $10M–$20M ARR. Below that threshold, HubSpot's simplicity and cost-effectiveness usually outweigh Salesforce's power. Above it, the complexity of the sales process often justifies Salesforce's overhead. Many companies start on HubSpot and migrate to Salesforce as they scale — a path that is well-trodden enough to be manageable with proper planning.</p>
  <p>One important caveat: if your company is already deeply integrated with the Salesforce ecosystem (Marketing Cloud, Service Cloud, or a large AppExchange footprint), the switching cost to HubSpot may outweigh the benefits even at smaller scale. Evaluate the full stack, not just the CRM in isolation.</p>
</section>
